---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="ALTA Foods — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="ALTA Foods runs four fully automated tortilla lines around the clock. With Formic, it's halving end-of-line staffing and ending the churn of its highest-turnover job — palletizing."
  ogTitle="ALTA Foods — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="4 lines · 60 annual hires removed · zero upfront CapEx"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/alta-foods" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>ALTA Foods
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · ALTA Foods</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.8vw,56px)">Charting the Future: ALTA Foods Expands Automation to Strengthen Operations</h1>
    <p class="lede">ALTA Foods runs four fully automated tortilla lines around the clock — but case packing and palletizing still pulled up to four people per line. With Formic, ALTA is cutting that in half and ending the churn of its highest-turnover job.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <img src="/stories/alta-foods-hero.jpg" alt="ALTA Foods tortilla production line" />
      <span class="dv-cap">ALTA Foods · tortilla production</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:64px 0 0">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 80px">
    <div class="db-tag">At a glance</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">In business</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">18 years</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Industry</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Tortilla manufacturing</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Lines</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">4 production lines</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Schedule</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">24 hrs/day · 5 days/wk</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Automated</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Mixing → bagging</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>Automated everywhere <em>but the end of the line</em>.</h2>
      <p>ALTA runs four lines, 24 hours a day, five days a week — fully automated from mixing to bagging. But case packing and palletizing still required up to four workers per line. Palletizing is also a high-turnover entry job: historically 12 palletizing roles turned over four times a year — 60 people, roughly 120 applications, plus drug-testing and onboarding costs every year.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>4 lines, 24/5, automated from mixing to bagging</li>
        <li>Up to 4 workers per line at the end of line</li>
        <li>12 roles × 4 turnovers = 60 hires a year</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Robotic palletizer at the end of a tortilla line" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">End of line · automated</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Formic Full Service palletizing cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Full Service · yearly contract</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>Cut the line crew, <em>not the people</em>.</h2>
      <p>Automating palletizing cuts end-of-line staffing from four to two — two monitoring machinery, two redeployed to more critical tasks — with case packing automation following. ALTA historically bought and managed its own equipment, but switched to Formic's Full Service model: no upfront CapEx and a yearly contract, freeing capital for future strategic projects.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>End-of-line crew cut from 4 to 2 per line</li>
        <li>Full Service: no CapEx, yearly contract</li>
        <li>Case packing automation next</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:88px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <blockquote>"With Formic, it didn't even come down to the cost of those employees palletizing... What is the cost of not those 12 people, but those 60 people every year?"</blockquote>
      <cite>Don Barnes · President, ALTA Foods</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Fewer hires to chase. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">More capital to deploy.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">4</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Production lines</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">60</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Annual hires removed</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">$0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Upfront CapEx</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Chart your <em>automation future</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
